article.headline: North Texas 98, Troy 57
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis and Calvin Watson scored 19 points apiece and North Texas capitalized on Troy's poor shooting in the Mean Green's 98-57 victory on Thursday night. North Texas (15-7, 6-5 Sun Belt) led 42-30 at halftime and pulled away in the second half with 67 percent field goal shooting for the period to 31 percent for Troy. The Mean Green took its biggest lead, a 41-point margin, as time expired. The win marked North Texas' most lopsided Sun Belt victory ever. Keith Wooden added 12 points for North Texas and Justin Howerton came off the bench to grab seven rebounds. Michael Sturns led the team with six assists. O'Darien Bassett and Justin Jonus scored 10 apiece for Troy (9-14, 4-8), making them the only Trojans in double figures. Richard Chaney had six rebounds. North Texas shot 57 percent from the field for the game to Troy's 26 percent. North Texas outrebounded Troy 52-31.
